# macOS
.DS_Store

# Patronus deploy products — what `patronus install --local` writes into a project.
# None of these are source (Patronus's own artifacts live under artifacts/); they
# are generated per-project install output and must never be committed. Covers all
# three target tools (Claude / Codex / OpenCode). NOTE: .gitignore does not support
# inline comments — each pattern is on its own line.
#   .claude/          Claude: skills, hooks, output-styles, settings.json
#   .codex/           Codex: config.toml, AGENTS.md
#   .config/opencode/ OpenCode: opencode.json, AGENTS.md
#   .patronus/        Patronus install state (state.json, cache, fetched binaries)
#   CLAUDE.md         appended instruction target (Claude)
#   .mcp.json         merged MCP-server config (Claude project scope)
.claude/
.codex/
.config/opencode/
.patronus/
/CLAUDE.md
/.mcp.json
# patronus.lock is intentionally NOT ignored — it is the committed lock spec, the
# one Patronus product meant to live in version control.
#
# /AGENTS.md is likewise NOT ignored. It is still install output (composed from the
# instruction artifacts, same as CLAUDE.md), but it is the AGENTS.md-format contract
# this repo asks every agent to read — so it is tracked and reviewable rather than
# invisible. The tradeoff: re-running `patronus install` can produce a diff here, and
# that diff is the signal that the composed instructions changed. Commit it with the
# artifact change that caused it.

# Patronus CI output (published to GitHub Releases)
/registry/

# Go build artifacts
/patronus
/dist/

# Local planning/design docs — kept out of version control. The canonical home is
# local-specs/ (a gitignored folder); the root-level patterns below still catch a
# stray DESIGN.md/design-*.md/plan.md left at the repo root.
local-specs/
DESIGN.md
design-*.md
plan.md
# …but vendored skill/artifact content is legitimate even when a file happens to
# be named like a design doc (e.g. codebase-design's DESIGN-IT-TWICE.md). The
# design-doc rules above are for ROOT-LEVEL planning artifacts; never let them
# sweep up tracked catalog content under artifacts/.
!artifacts/**

# Local R2 audit creds — never commit
.r2-audit.env

# Local env / secrets — never commit
.env
